cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper is about deep learning applied to natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically focusing on the use of indirect supervision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a framework that combines probabilistic logic with deep learning, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of variational EM, which is a common optimization technique in probabilistic graphical models, falling under the category of cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach that combines domain and linguistic knowledge, which could also fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
